(method) String.startsWith(searchString: string, position?: number | undefined): boolean

Returns true if the sequence of elements of searchString converted to a String is the same as the corresponding elements of this object (converted to a String) starting at position. Otherwise returns false.
data.4899:
(method) Array<T>.find<S extends T>(predicate: (this: void, value: T, index: number, obj: T[]) => value is S, thisArg?: any): S | undefined (+1 overload)

Returns the value of the first element in the array where predicate is true, and undefined otherwise.
data.8250:
(method) String.repeat(count: number): string

Returns a String value that is made from count copies appended together. If count is 0, the empty string is returned.
